org.osmdroid.bonuspack.kml
Class KmlFeature

java.lang.Object
  org.osmdroid.bonuspack.kml.KmlFeature
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
Direct Known Subclasses:
KmlFolder, KmlGroundOverlay, KmlPlacemark
public abstract class KmlFeature
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable

The Java representation of a KML Feature. It currently supports: Folder, Document, GroundOverlay, and Placemark with the following Geometry: Point, LineString, or Polygon.
This is an abstract class, actual Features must use sub-classes: - Folder feature is a KmlFolder.
- Document feature is a KmlFolder, handled exactly like a Folder.
- GroundOverlay feature is a KmlGroundOverlay. - Placemark feature is a KmlPlacemark.

Author:
M.Kergall
See Also:
KmlDocument, KML Reference

buildOverlay

public abstract org.osmdroid.views.overlay.Overlay buildOverlay(org.osmdroid.views.MapView map,
                                                                Style defaultStyle,
                                                                KmlFeature.Styler styler,
                                                                KmlDocument kmlDocument)
Build the Overlay related to this KML object. If this is a Folder, recursively build overlays from Folder items. Styling strategy is following this order of priority: 1) the styler 2) or if null, style of the Feature, 3) or if not defined, defaultStyle 4) or if null, hard-coded default values.

Parameters:
map -
defaultStyle - to apply when an Feature has no Style defined.
styler - Styler that will be applied to Features and Geometries.
kmlDocument - for styles
Returns:
the Overlay related to this KML object class.
